<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4570377>
    dc:description "Fig. 1.—Adult Lepus europaeus, gender unknown, industrial area near Hamburg, Germany, July 2017. Photograph by A. Bock." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4570377/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4570379>
    dc:description "Fig. 2.—Dorsal, ventral, and lateral views of skull and lateral view of mandible of an adult male of Lepus europaeus, collection locality Schwarzenbek, Germany, 02.12.1997, specimen number 8933 (468), Zoological Museum, University of Hamburg, greatest length of skull 95 mm. Photograph by A. Bock." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4570379/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4570382>
    dc:description "Fig. 3.—Distribution of Lepus europaeus. Subspecies shown are 1), L. e. europaeus original distribution = yellow areas, introduced = orange areas; 2) L. e. occidentalis; 3) L. e. creticus; 4) L. e. cyprius; 5) L. e. hybridus; 6) L. e. parnassius; 7) L. e. rhodius; 8) L. e. syriacus; 9) L. e. transsylvanicus. Possible subspecies of Greece (L. e. caspicus, L. e. connori, L. e. cyrensis, L. e. judeae, L. e. karpathorum, L. e. medius, L. e. ponticus, see text for details) are not on map. Map modeled in Quantum GIS 2.4 (Chugiak) by A. Bock (2015), based on information and maps from Chapman and Flux (1990), Slimen et al. (2008), Krapp (2003), Masseti (2012), Reid (2011), Thulin et al. (2006)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4570382/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4570384>
    dc:description "Fig. 4.—Juvenile Lepus europaeus born in early 2020, gender unknown, industrial area near Hamburg, Germany, May 2020. Photograph by A. Bock." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4570384/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4570388>
    dc:description "Fig. 5.—Lepus europaeus in typical habitat near Hamburg, Germany. Photograph by A. Bock." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4570388/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

